           I work in Python, C++, JavaScript, and Rust, and I like the kind of problem-solving that rewards patience, a habit I picked up competing in the European Girls' Mathematical Olympiad (top 10 in Ireland) and the national Programming Olympiad finals. I'm happiest when I'm building something real: I co-founded <a href="/portfolio#lynra">Lynra</a> at Dublin's Patch accelerator, training an object-detection model and putting it on a rover that delivers micro-injections to diseased ash trees. Earlier, a four-person team and I won SciFest's Technology Category and the EirGrid Award for a carbon-capture filter that used CAD and 3D printing to cut CO₂ from car exhausts. More recently I built SÓShielta at Hack Europe with a four-person team.
